# 🤖 SentinelCodeAI

### AI-Powered GitHub Pull Request Reviews — Fully Local

A GitHub App that automatically reviews pull requests using a **locally hosted LLM** through Ollama.  
No OpenAI API key. No cloud dependency. No subscription cost.

---

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.11+-3776AB?style=for-the-badge&logo=python&logoColor=white)
![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/FastAPI-009688?style=for-the-badge&logo=fastapi&logoColor=white)
![Ollama](https://img.shields.io/badge/Ollama-qwen2.5--coder:7b-black?style=for-the-badge)
![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/badge/GitHub-App-181717?style=for-the-badge&logo=github&logoColor=white)

</div>

---

# ✨ Features

- 🔍 Automatically reviews every pull request
- 🧠 Uses a local LLM through Ollama
- 🔒 Verifies GitHub webhook signatures with HMAC-SHA256
- 💬 Posts structured AI review comments directly on PRs
- ⚡ No external AI API required
- 🛠 Lightweight FastAPI backend

---

# ⚙️ How It Works

1. A developer opens or updates a pull request
2. GitHub sends a webhook event to the FastAPI server
3. The server verifies the webhook signature
4. The PR diff is fetched from GitHub
5. The diff is analyzed by a local LLM through Ollama
6. SentinelCodeAI posts an automated review comment

---

# 🧠 Review Categories

SentinelCodeAI analyzes pull requests for:

- 🐛 Bugs & Logic Errors
- 🔒 Security Issues
- ⚡ Performance Problems
- 💡 Improvement Suggestions
- ✅ Overall Summary

---

# 🛠 Tech Stack

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Python | Core backend |
| FastAPI | Webhook API server |
| Uvicorn | ASGI server |
| Ollama | Local LLM hosting |
| qwen2.5-coder:7b | Code review model |
| GitHub Apps API | GitHub integration |
| JWT Authentication | Secure app authentication |
| ngrok | Local webhook tunneling |

---

# 📁 Project Structure

```txt
SentinelCodeAI/
├── main.py
├── github_auth.py
├── github_client.py
├── reviewer.py
├── .env
└── private-key.pem
````

### File Overview

| File               | Description                             |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| `main.py`          | FastAPI webhook server                  |
| `github_auth.py`   | JWT + installation token authentication |
| `github_client.py` | GitHub API communication                |
| `reviewer.py`      | LLM review generation logic             |
| `.env`             | Environment variables                   |
| `private-key.pem`  | GitHub App private key                  |

---

# 🚀 Setup

## 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/aminabk99/SentinelCodeAI
cd SentinelCodeAI
```

---

## 2. Create a Virtual Environment

### Windows

```bash
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### macOS / Linux

```bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

## 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install fastapi uvicorn requests PyJWT cryptography python-dotenv
```

---

## 4. Install Ollama

Download Ollama:

https://ollama.com

Then pull the model:

```bash
ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:7b
```

---

# 🔑 GitHub App Setup

Go to:

GitHub → Settings → Developer Settings → GitHub Apps → **New GitHub App**

---

## Required Permissions

### Repository Permissions

| Permission    | Access       |
| ------------- | ------------ |
| Pull Requests | Read & Write |
| Contents      | Read-only    |

---

## Subscribe to Events

Enable:

* Pull request events

---

## Save These Values

You will need:

* GitHub App ID
* Webhook Secret
* Private Key (`.pem` file)

Then install the app on your repository.

---

# 🧾 Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file:

```env
GITHUB_APP_ID=your_app_id
GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=private-key.pem
GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_secret
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5-coder:7b
```

---

# ▶️ Running the Project

Open **3 terminals**.

---

## Terminal 1 — Start Ollama

```bash
ollama serve
```

---

## Terminal 2 — Start FastAPI

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

---

## Terminal 3 — Start ngrok

```bash
ngrok http 8000
```

Copy your ngrok forwarding URL and update your GitHub App webhook:

```txt
https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok-free.dev/webhook
```

---

# 🧪 Testing

Open a pull request on any repository where the app is installed.

SentinelCodeAI should automatically post a review comment.

---

## Health Check

Visit:

```txt
https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok-free.dev/health
```

Expected response:

```json
{"status":"ok"}
```

---

# 🔒 Security

* `.env` and `private-key.pem` should NEVER be committed
* All webhook requests are verified using HMAC-SHA256
* GitHub App authentication uses short-lived JWTs
* Installation tokens are scoped to individual repositories

---

# 🧩 Hardest Part

The most difficult part of the project was implementing GitHub App authentication correctly.

GitHub Apps require:

* JWT generation using RSA private keys
* Exchanging JWTs for installation tokens
* Proper webhook verification
* Accurate timing and expiration handling

Debugging failed authentication and silent `401 Unauthorized` responses required extensive testing.

---

# 💡 Most Interesting Part

The most interesting discovery was how strongly prompt engineering affects model quality.

Small prompt changes dramatically improved:

* formatting consistency
* issue accuracy
* hallucination reduction
* review usefulness

Explicit instructions like:

> “Never hallucinate issues not present in the diff”

significantly improved review reliability.

